The FAR has been used by many studies to quantify the anthropogenic influence on the occurrence of recent extreme events and its fate in projected scenarios. The FAR basically addresses the question of what fraction of extremes (in our case 2-year consecutive drought) occurring in Central European region is attributable to anthropogenic influence, and is given by,4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
