				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{0}$$\end{document}P0 is the probability of exceeding a 2-year consecutive drought without anthropogenic influence (HistNat) and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{1}$$\end{document}P1 is with the anthropogenic influence40 (RCP scenarios). The FAR value near to 1 indicates the nearly certain human influence in causing the 2-year consecutive drought.
